    <PrimAttribute name="sequenced" id="27a3fb45-8af5-4acf-b6ac-da4db68112f3">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>This is used to denote if the TI on the Request has been PLANNED, i.e. that the TI has a planned future move.

This allows us to then set the WLE to complete when the Req is sequenced but the TI has no planned location.

This is needed at the colour coding stage when the TI is not planned. At this point sequenced will be false.

When the TI is planned the SlotRequest sequenced is set to true.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
